commits.commitMessage:
Update rfcombos python scripts for SDX65

Update rfcombos generate script for SDX65:
- ability to parse Sierra rf features spreadsheet
- support for specifying maximum bandwidth for NR bands(currently hardcoded)
- support NR CA combos

Also separates SDX55 and SDX65 scripts into different folders.
rfcombos parsing script is also updated by adding additional bands
supported by EM929x

Resolves: QTIX65-217
Change-Id: I5586879b600c33c5ecfb1b6c943055e71fe7e5b8
Signed-off-by: Santhosh Thota <sthota@sierrawireless.com>
commits.subject: Update rfcombos python scripts for SDX65

comments.message:
Comparing the sdx55 version, the two generate.py files are very similar. Is it viable to have one script? Or is it not worth the effort?
Wondering if it will get confusing if there are two different version strings that may at one time have the same value in the future?

Big part of the script is dependent on the input spreadsheet's format.
I plan on splitting the spreadsheet dependent part out but, it's not urgent for now. Until then, I think it's better leave the SDX55 script untouched.
I missed to increase the version number. Will update.

commits.commitMessage:
Update rfcombos.py script to handle combos with no UL

Description:
The rfcombos.py script fails in a not-so-nice way when it comes across
combos with no UL band (which is currently happening due to the issue
addressed in FERRARI-2339). The script should be updated to handle these
combos more gracefully.

Solution:
Made the script skip over combos with no UL band.
Note: also added B43 to the list of accepted LTE bands.

Resolves: QTIX5510-3312
Related: FERRARI-2339
Change-Id: I724990fd765ee1fc3f9f6b95e5839e2391603ac6
commits.subject: Update rfcombos.py script to handle combos with no UL

comments.message: Also added B43 to this list as I'm seeing it in recent combo lists. Are there any other bands that should be added here?
When compared to the PTS, B43 is the only one that we were missing.

commits.commitMessage:
Add script to generate RFC combos from QTI combo list

Added generate.py script that generates CA/ENDC combinations in RFC format from the 3gpp format in Qualcomm's RF combos list.
Also added the Qualcomm's combos list customized to the support of Sierra's EM9x products.

Resolves: QTIX5510-2974
Change-Id: Iac5eec0f01678618f639db635b97ee9684ff6130
Signed-off-by: Santhosh Thota <sthota@sierrawireless.com>
commits.subject: Add script to generate RFC combos from QTI combo list

comments.message: There are newer versions (80-PM475-650_R and 80-PM671-651_J). Should we use those?

Checked in these new files. The script works for these revisions too but the combos we currently implemented are based ver P & H files.
Need to review the differences closely but, there are some additions/differences for FR1 combos and minor differences for LTE combos.

Considering that our FW is close to MR, do you think we should review to see anymore combos can be added now?
It may be wise to do a quick summary of the changes, particularly focused on ATT/VZW/TMO impacts.
Needs a file header similar to rfcombos.py (purpose and copyright)
